<html>
{{> head}}
<script>

    $(function () {
        $('[data-toggle="tooltip"]').tooltip();
    });

    function showPanel(name) {

        $("#what-panel").hide();
        $("#who-panel").hide();
        $("#how-panel").hide();

        $("#what-panel-toggle").removeClass('active');
        $("#who-panel-toggle").removeClass('active');
        $("#how-panel-toggle").removeClass('active');

        $("#" + name).show();
        $("#" + name + "-toggle").addClass('active');

    }

    function adjustButtons() {

        //xs : width < 768 px
        //sm : width < 992 px
        //md : width < 1200 px
        //lg : width > 1200 px

        //Calculate how tall the buttons should be based on the info panel size.
        //height of button-spacers is 20 px each, there are 2 total, hence -40.

        var h = ($("#info-panel").height() - 40)/3;

        $(".main-button").css('height', h+"px");

    }

</script>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <div class="row" style="height:35%;">
    </div>
    <div class='row' style="">
        <div class='col-md-6'>
            <div id='info-panel' class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <h3>Welcome to Acuta's Bigdata App!</h3>
                    <hr>
                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-xs-3" style="min-width:100px">
                            <ul class="nav nav-pills nav-stacked">
                                <li role="presentation" id="what-panel-toggle" class="active"><a
                                        onclick="showPanel('what-panel');" href="#">What</a></li>
                                <li role="presentation" id="who-panel-toggle" class=""><a
                                        onclick="showPanel('who-panel');" href="#">Who</a></li>
                                <li role="presentation" id="how-panel-toggle" class=""><a
                                        onclick="showPanel('how-panel');" href="#">How</a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-sm-8">
                            <div id="what-panel">

                                <p>Bigdata is a web application created by <a href="http://actua.ca">Actua</a> as part of
                                    the <a href="http://www.actua.ca/codemakers/">Google Code Makers Project</a> to
                                    support Computer Science education in Canada.</p>

                                <p>The Bigdata application provides a platform to experiment with the concepts of data
                                    analysis and data mining!</p>

                                <p>To learn more about Bigdata, see the <a href="#">video tutorial</a></p>

                            </div>
                            <div id="who-panel" hidden="true">

                                <p>You! All of the data for the Bigdata app comes for the users. You can enter data by going to the <a href="student">Student</a> page.</p>

                                <p>This application is open to the public, but it was intended for use by educators to teach concepts related to Computer Science and Statistics.</p>

                                <p>Bigdata was created by the <a href="http://actua.ca/codemakers">Codemakers</a> team at <a href="http://actua.ca">Actua</a> with support from <a href="http://google.com">Google</a>.</p>

                            </div>
                            <div id="how-panel" hidden="true">

                                <p>Bigdata is a web application that collects data provided by users. The data is stored in a database and then analyzed. The data can then be used to predict properties of new objects.</p>

                                <p>The application predictions properties of new data using a technique called data mining. More specifically, it uses a statistical approach called a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naive_Bayes_classifier">Naive Bayes Classifier</a></p>

                                <p>To learn more about how the Bigdata application works under the hood, check out the <a href="#">video tutorial</a></p>

                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="center-block col-md-6">
            <a href='student'>
                <button type="button" style="background-color:#6FBF51;color:white;"
                        class="main-button main-button-lg btn btn-success btn-lg btn-block" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Click here to submit new data!">Students
                </button>
            </a>
            <div class="button-spacer"></div>
            <a href='instructor'>
                <button type="button" style="background-color:#FF9900;color:white;"
                        class="main-button main-button-lg btn btn-lg btn-block" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Click here to create a new data set and classifier.">Instructors
                </button>
            </a>
            <div class="button-spacer"></div>
            <a href='minedata'>
                <button type="button" style="background-color:#FF4791;color:white;"
                        class="main-button main-button-lg btn btn-lg btn-block" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Click here to create view a data set and mine the data!">Mine Data
                </button>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
<script>
    $(window).resize(function () {
        adjustButtons();
    });

    adjustButtons(); //call this once so that the correct size is chosen for the buttons
</script>
</html>
